<A>__{the sound of laughter is considerably dimmed in here; it's barely audible. but there is another sound, a shifting sound in the corner of the room. she reaches for the light switch, and turns it on. the bulb's been broken however. she stares around the room, trying to make sense of the shadows. nervously, she approaches the wall, on which four streaks of light from the window fall. now she looks towards the window and realizes that the newspaper has been torn, as if by four fingers. her breath catches. suddenly, she's afraid. she stands absolutely still, eyes wide in the gloom.}
